Client doesn't need to know the implementation
Exactly like you said. The client only knows:

Tool name → get_forecast
What it does → "Get weather forecast for a location"
What it needs → latitude, longitude

It has no idea you're hitting the NWS API, how you're parsing the JSON, or anything else under the hood.

3. Swap the implementation without breaking anything
Tomorrow you could switch from NWS API to OpenWeatherMap or AccuWeather — and no client needs to change. They still just call get_forecast.

4. Reusable across teams and projects
If your company has a database, internal API, or business tool — wrap it in an MCP server once and every developer on the team can use it in their AI tools instantly.

5. AI decides when to use it
You don't have to tell Claude "use the weather tool." Claude figures it out on its own based on the conversation — making your tools feel like a natural extension of the AI.



